{1 Eliom client API}

{2 modules with interface close to server side}

The {!Eliom_pervasives} module should be opened in every client side
code, it extands some stdlib modules and provides functions to build
XML and HTML trees.

{!Eliom_output.Html5} is used to build forms.

{!Eliom_services} on client side only provides void_coservices and non
localised service parameters.

{!modules:
Eliom_pervasives
Eliom_pervasives.XML
Eliom_pervasives.HTML5
Eliom_output.Html5
Eliom_services
}

{2 modules with interface different from server side}

The {!Eliom_bus}, {!Eliom_comet} and {!Eliom_react} modules provides
client/server communications facilities.

{!Eliom_client} provides functions to call services and move to another url.

{!modules:
Eliom_client
Eliom_bus
Eliom_comet
Eliom_react
}
